item.title: Need help Compiling Errors So far....(6)
item.dc:creator: @Java_Is_My_Bitch Java Is My Bitch™
item.description:
@Java_Is_My_Bitch wrote:

Would help if ya posted the code.

The amount of )'s exceeds the amount of ('s, or as far as i could tell.

if((pla(557, 4) == true ) ( () ) ( ( )) ))
(What i wrote, i understand myself)

For every ( there has to be a )

So its an EVEN number, EVERYTIME! Just like brackets, opening and closing.

Post the code, maybe i could help you out.

–

The error on:

fromBank(etc) {

Is that your missing a bracket, maybe you just added a command, and it’s missing a bracket.

As for the rest, once you’ve fixed the bracket problem for the command you might of just added, the rest will go away, otherwise, post and tell me.
